txt.en: 'What is this meat? You got it from what? Ugh, it smells foul! I only hope we will soon move on to the Dale-lands, where we can eat meat fit for Men again!'
Tuhâl seems to have something to say about the Jangovar's orders.\n\nYou should talk to Tuhâl, who can be found in Utterby.
Animals can be found among the scrublands of the Ironfold.\n\nYou should hunt animals for their meat.
You should bring the meat to Kúlkhur, who can be found inside Utterby.
The food stores of Utterby are beginning to run out, so the Easterlings must turn to the local fauna for meat.

'What do they expect? I have not seen any deer or boar here, have you? I suppose we will just have to hunt what we can find out in the scrub and make due. We should save some of what we find, as well. The Jangovar have been keeping all the food for themselves, leaving everyone else to go hungry.'

'Come here, Chayasír. If you really want to be useful, go hunting for us. The food left by the Dalish is running low, and we must find more. It seems there are few game animals here to hunt, but that is your problem to figure out!'
'What is this meat? You got it from what? Ugh, it smells foul! I only hope we will soon move on to the Dale-lands, where we can eat meat fit for Men again!'
'What is this meat? You got it from what? Ugh, it smells foul! I only hope we will soon return to the Dale-lands, where we can eat meat fit for men again!'
